<div class="plain-box"><h2>New and updated genomes</h2>

<p>This bumper release of <a href="https://plants.ensembl.org/index.html">Ensembl Plants</a> brings eight new genomes, including <a href="https://plants.ensembl.org/Manihot_esculenta">cassava</a>, <a href="https://plants.ensembl.org/Gossypium_raimondii">cotton</a>, <a href="https://plants.ensembl.org/Cucumis_sativus">cucumber</a>, <a href="https://plants.ensembl.org/Phaseolus_vulgaris">green bean</a>, <a href="https://plants.ensembl.org/Helianthus_annuus">sunflower</a> and <a href="https://plants.ensembl.org/Dioscorea_rotundata">yam</a>. In addition we have updated to latest and greatly improved (v3.0) <a href="https://plants.ensembl.org/Sorghum_bicolor">sorghum</a> genome assembly from JGI as well as updated assemblies for both <a href="https://plants.ensembl.org/Glycine_max">soybean</a> and <a href="https://plants.ensembl.org/Prunus_persica">peach</a>. Users can now <a href="http://plants.ensembl.org/Arabidopsis_lyrata/Gene/Compara_Tree?g=Al_scaffold_0002_1120">view</a>, <a href="http://plants.ensembl.org/biomart/martview?VIRTUALSCHEMANAME=plants_mart&ATTRIBUTES=hvulgare_eg_gene.default.homologs.ensembl_gene_id|hvulgare_eg_gene.default.homologs.taestivum_eg_homolog_ensembl_gene|hvulgare_eg_gene.default.homologs.athaliana_eg_homolog_ensembl_gene|hvulgare_eg_gene.default.homologs.athaliana_eg_homolog_associated_gene_name&FILTERS=&VISIBLEPANEL=resultspanel">query</a>, <a href="ftp://ftp.ensemblgenomes.org/pub/release-38/plants/emf/ensembl-compara/homologies/">download</a> and <a href="https://www.ensembl.org/info/docs/api/compara/index.html">analyse</a> our comparative analysis of nearly 2 million genes across 53 plant species.</p>

<h2>New barley genome</h2>

<p>A ten-nation consortium has reported the first high-quality reference genome sequence of <a href="http://plants.ensembl.org/Hordeum_vulgare" title="Hordeum vulgare in Ensembl Plants"><em>Hordeum vulgare</em></a> (barley). The barley genome was sequenced and assembled using an array of state-of- the-art methods, taking ten years. For the first time, scientists can now locate all genes precisely in the genome and analyze complex gene families that play a key role in malting and resilience.</p>

<h2>New Arabidopsis variation data from the 1001 Genomes Project</h2>

<p>We have upgraded our representation of genetic variation in <a href="http://plants.ensembl.org/Arabidopsis_thaliana" title="Arabidopsis thaliana in Ensembl Plants">Arabidopsis thaliana</a>, incorporating the full data set from the <a href="http://1001genomes.org/" title="1001genomes.org">1001 Genomes Project</a>, covering more than 10 million variant loci across 1,135 samples (<a href="http://europepmc.org/abstract/MED/27293186" title="Europe PMC">Cell 2016</a>).</p></div>
